<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/"><channel><title>JavaScript on Starslayerx' Blog</title><link>https://starslayerx.github.io/tags/javascript/</link><description>Recent content in JavaScript on Starslayerx' Blog</description><image><title>Starslayerx' Blog</title><url>https://starslayerx.github.io/images/og-default.avif</url><link>https://starslayerx.github.io/images/og-default.avif</link></image><generator>Hugo -- 0.154.5</generator><language>en-US</language><lastBuildDate>Thu, 23 Oct 2025 08:00:00 +0800</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://starslayerx.github.io/tags/javascript/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Morden Javascript Tutorial Chapter 3.1 - Code Quailty</title><link>https://starslayerx.github.io/posts/morden-javascript-tutorial-chapter-3.1-code-quailty/</link><pubDate>Thu, 23 Oct 2025 08:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://starslayerx.github.io/posts/morden-javascript-tutorial-chapter-3.1-code-quailty/</guid><description>&lt;h3 id="31-debugging-in-the-browser"&gt;3.1 Debugging in the browser&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Debugging is the process of finding and fixing errors with a script.
All morden browsers and most other environments support debugging tools - a special UI in developer tools that makes debugging much easier.
It also allows to trace the code step by step to see what exactly is going on.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id="the-sources-panel"&gt;The &amp;ldquo;Sources&amp;rdquo; panel&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Sources panel has 3 parts:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;File Navigator&lt;/strong&gt; pane lists HTML, Javascript, CSS and other files, including images that are attatched to the page. Chrome extensions may appera here too.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Code Editor&lt;/strong&gt; pane shows the source code.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Javascript Debugging&lt;/strong&gt; pane is for debugging, we&amp;rsquo;ll explore it soon.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h4 id="console"&gt;Console&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;按 &lt;code&gt;Esc&lt;/code&gt; 可以打开控制台，在其中可以输入命令，按回车执行。&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Morden Javascript Tutorial Chapter 2 - Fundamentals: 11~18</title><link>https://starslayerx.github.io/posts/morden-javascript-tutorial-chapter-2-fundamentals-11~18/</link><pubDate>Sun, 21 Sep 2025 08:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://starslayerx.github.io/posts/morden-javascript-tutorial-chapter-2-fundamentals-11~18/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="211-logical-operators"&gt;2.11 Logical operators&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are four logical operators in JavaScript: &lt;code&gt;||&lt;/code&gt; (ORA), &lt;code&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/code&gt; (AND), &lt;code&gt;!&lt;/code&gt; (NOT), &lt;code&gt;??&lt;/code&gt; (Nullish Coalescing 空值合并).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="-or"&gt;|| OR&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-JavaScript" data-lang="JavaScript"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;result&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;b&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;There are four logical combinations:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-JavaScript" data-lang="JavaScript"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;alter&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kc"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kc"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c1"&gt;// true
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;alert&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kc"&gt;false&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kc"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c1"&gt;// true
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;alert&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kc"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kc"&gt;false&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c1"&gt;// true
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;alert&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kc"&gt;false&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kc"&gt;false&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c1"&gt;// false
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;If an operand is not a boolean it&amp;rsquo;s converted to be a boolean for the evaluation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-JavaScript" data-lang="JavaScript"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mi"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c1"&gt;// works like (true || false)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;alter&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;truthy!&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4 id="or--finds-the-first-truthy-value"&gt;OR &amp;ldquo;||&amp;rdquo; finds the first truthy value&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-JavaScript" data-lang="JavaScript"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;result&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;value1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;value2&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;value3&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The OR &lt;code&gt;||&lt;/code&gt; operator does the following:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Morden Javascript Tutorial Chapter 2 - Fundamentals: 06~10</title><link>https://starslayerx.github.io/posts/morden-javascript-tutorial-chapter-2-fundamentals-06~10/</link><pubDate>Wed, 17 Sep 2025 08:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://starslayerx.github.io/posts/morden-javascript-tutorial-chapter-2-fundamentals-06~10/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="26-interaction-alert-prompt-confirm"&gt;2.6 Interaction: alert, prompt, confirm&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Will introduce &lt;code&gt;alert&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;prompt&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;confirm&lt;/code&gt; in this chapter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="alert"&gt;alert&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It shows a message and waits for the user to press &amp;ldquo;OK&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-JavaScript" data-lang="JavaScript"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;alert&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;Hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="prompt"&gt;prompt&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This function &lt;code&gt;prompt&lt;/code&gt; accepts two arguments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-JavaScript" data-lang="JavaScript"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;result&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;prompt&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nx"&gt;title&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;default&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;]);&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;It shows a modal window with a text message, an input field for the visitor, and the buttons OK/Cancel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;title&lt;/code&gt;: The text to show the visitor.
&lt;code&gt;default&lt;/code&gt;: An optional second parameter, the initial value for the input field.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Morden Javascript Tutorial Chapter 2 - Fundamentals: 01~05</title><link>https://starslayerx.github.io/posts/morden-javascript-tutorial-chapter-2-fundamentals-01~05/</link><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 08:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://starslayerx.github.io/posts/morden-javascript-tutorial-chapter-2-fundamentals-01~05/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="21-hellow-wrold"&gt;2.1 Hellow Wrold&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Firtly, let&amp;rsquo;s see how to attach a script to a webpage.
For server-side environments (like Node.js), you can execute this script with a command like &lt;code&gt;node my.js&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="the-script-tag"&gt;The &amp;ldquo;script&amp;rdquo; tag&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;JavaScript programs can be inserted almost anywhere into an HTML docuemnt using the &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;script&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; tag&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-html" data-lang="html"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="cp"&gt;&amp;lt;!DOCTYPE html&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;html&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;body&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;p&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;Before this script...&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;lt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;p&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;script&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="nx"&gt;alert&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;Hello, World!&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;lt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;script&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;p&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;...After the script...&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;lt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;p&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;lt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;body&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;lt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;html&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;script&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; tag contains JavaScript code which is automatically executed when the browser process the tag.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Morden Javascript Tutorial Chapter 1 - An Introduction</title><link>https://starslayerx.github.io/posts/morden-javascript-tutorial-chapter-1-an-introduction/</link><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 08:00:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://starslayerx.github.io/posts/morden-javascript-tutorial-chapter-1-an-introduction/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="an-introduction-to-javascript"&gt;An Introduction to JavaScript&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let’s see what’s so special about JavaScript, what we can achieve with it, and what other technologies play well with it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="why-is-it-call-javascript"&gt;Why is it call JavaScript?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;JavaScript initially called &amp;ldquo;Live Script&amp;rdquo;. But Java was popular at that time, so it was decided that positioning a new language as a &amp;ldquo;younger brother&amp;rdquo; of Java would help.
But as it evolved, JavaScript became a fully independent language with its won specification called &lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ECMAScript"&gt;ECMAScript&lt;/a&gt;, and now it has no relation to Java at all.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>